long_description: the pakistan mathematical society (پاکستان ریاضیاتی معاشرہ, acronym: pakms), is a learned society for mathematical sciences, possibly the largest learned society of its own kind, and a research institute to promote mathematics in the country. the pakistan mathematical society is an association of professional mathematicians dedicated to promote mathematical science and research and interest in the country. the organization annually published various publications, and held conferences as well as annual monetary awards and prizes to mathematicians.
